// File          : TC_18.java
// Package       : stepdefinitions
// Description   : Step definitions shared across TC_18 (Overclaim), TC_19 (Dual Claim)
//                 and TC_20 (No Agricultural Activity) Preliminary Checks automation.
//
//                 Herd numbers and agent usernames are resolved at runtime from:
//                   BISS_DATA — vwbs_land_validation (LVS_DESC = ‘Pending’)
//                   BISS_INET — tdcr_user_info / tdco_customer_asscs
//                 via the @Before(”@preliminary”) hook in Hooks.java.
//
//                 The core step “the agent opens a farmer dashboard for preliminary check herd {string}”
//                 performs THREE layers of UI validation before proceeding:
//
//                   Layer 3A — My Clients search must return at least 1 row
//                   Layer 3B — The returned row must NOT be marked “Herd expired”
//                   Layer 3C — The Preliminary Checks tab must show at least 1 record
//
//                 On any Layer 3 failure:
//                   1. Re-query BISS_DATA at next offset for this check type
//                   2. Validate new herd against BISS_INET
//                   3. If agent changed → logout → login as new agent → navigate to My Clients
//                   4. Retry — up to MAX_UI_RETRIES attempts total
//
//                 All locators are externalised to ObjectRepository.properties.
//                 All iAction calls follow framework conventions:
//                   local vars: i prefix | params: p prefix
//                   ObjReader.getLocator(“key”) — never raw XPath inline
//
// Author        : Aniket Pathare | aniket.pathare@government.ie
// Date Created  : 17-04-2026 | Updated : 20-04-2026 (3-layer retry + expired herd check)
